OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1774185071
OL,3,CDad who lost son to Meningitis B calls
OL,4,Cfor all teenagers to be vaccinated
OL,6,FIt comes as he number of cases of
OL,7,Fmeningitis linked to an outbreak in
OL,8,FKent has risen to 34, health officials
OL,9,Fhave confirmed on Saturday.
OL,11,F"He was a very bouncy little boy, and
OL,12,FI remember the night before, he didn't
OL,13,Fwant to go to bed," Toby said.
OL,15,F"I think I got up about 1, gave him
OL,16,Fhis bottle - but he didn't want it,
OL,17,Fwhich is really unusual.
OL,19,F"In the morning, he was definitely not
OL,20,Fhimself, but I felt he was fine for me
OL,21,Fto go to work.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1774185071
OL,3,CDad who lost son to Meningitis B calls
OL,4,Cfor all teenagers to be vaccinated
OL,6,F"I went to work, and I was in Tooting,
OL,7,Fworking in Blackfriars at the time,
OL,8,Fand then 40 minutes later, Caroline,
OL,9,Fmy wife, called me and said, 'we're
OL,10,Fbeing blue-lighted to hospital, they
OL,11,Fthink he's got meningitis.'"
OL,13,FZack was diagnosed with meningococcal
OL,14,Fsepticaemia and put in an induced
OL,15,Fcoma, but deteriorated rapidy, and
OL,16,Fdied in hospital.
OL,18,FDescribing the disease, Toby said
OL,19,F"it's brutal."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1774185071
OL,3,CDad who lost son to Meningitis B calls
OL,4,Cfor all teenagers to be vaccinated
OL,6,F"It's devastating," he added.
OL,7,F"Statistically, if you contract
OL,8,Fmeningitis B, you've got a 1 in 10
OL,9,Fchance of dying.
OL,11,F"You've got basically 5 out of 10
OL,12,Fchance of being left with life-
OL,13,Fchanging disabilities.
OL,15,F"It is a disease you just do not want
OL,16,Fto contract.
OL,18,F"It's just the speed of it - as far as
OL,19,Fwe were concerned, he was teething in
OL,20,Fthe morning to death 12 hours later."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
